# Polymarket API Guide

## Endpoints

| Purpose | Endpoint | Notes |
|---------|----------|-------|
| Get event by slug | `GET https://gamma-api.polymarket.com/events?slug={slug}` | Only exact slug match works |
| Get all FIFA WC matches | `GET https://gamma-api.polymarket.com/events?series_id=11433&closed=false&limit=200` | Single call, returns all match events |
| Text search | `GET https://api.copilot.markets/gamma/public-search?q={query}&limit_per_type=10` | Full-text search across all events |

## Fetching World Cup Match Predictions

Use `series_id=11433` to get all FIFA World Cup match events in one call. Do NOT guess slugs or iterate — slugs use inconsistent country codes and may change.

Each match typically has 3 event types — filter by title:
- **Match result**: "Mexico vs. South Africa" (use these)
- **Halftime**: title contains "Halftime Result" (skip unless needed)
- **Exact score**: title contains "Exact Score" (skip unless needed)

## Event Structure (key fields)

- `title`: match name, e.g. "Mexico vs. South Africa"
- `endDate`: match datetime (ISO 8601)
- `markets[]`: array of outcomes (win/draw/lose)
  - `groupItemTitle`: outcome label, e.g. "Mexico", "Draw (...)"
  - `outcomePrices`: JSON string `["0.665","0.335"]` — index 0 is Yes probability
  - `outcomePrices` can be `null` — always filter before `JSON.parse`
- `teams[]`: structured team data with `name`, `abbreviation`, `logo`, `ordering` (home/away)
- `series[].id`: `"11433"` for FIFA World Cup

## The Gamma events API does NOT support text search

Parameters like `title`, `text`, `search`, `tag`, `series`, `sport` are silently ignored and return default results. Only these filters work:
- `slug` (exact match)
- `series_id` (numeric ID)
- `tag_id` (numeric ID, e.g. `102232` for FIFA World Cup tag)
- `closed` (boolean)
- `limit` / `offset` (pagination)

For text search, use the `public-search` endpoint above.
